The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the study of menu complexity, which is related to computational complexity and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of approximation algorithms and optimization techniques suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and economic theory (cs.EC). Finally, the paper involves the study of information theory, as it considers the number of distinct (allocation, price) pairs that a bidder might receive (cs.IT).
